{In this chapter, we are going to deal with some very dubious attempts from
Black to avoid White's dangerous 8.Bb5. By doing this, Black goes out of the
frying pan into the fire.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6
6. e4 a6 {[#] With this move, Black tries to induce the natural 7.a4 in which
case after 7...g6 the game would have entered a playable line for black as Bb5
is ruled out. Fortunately for White, as soon will become clear, ...b5 is not a
threat.} (6... g6 7. f4 a6 8. e5 $1 {After this advance Black's is hopeless in
every line.} Nfd7 (8... Ng4 9. Nf3 Bg7 10. h3 Nh6 {1-0 (27) Motyka,
H-Maszkowski,T Poland 1995} 11. Ne4 dxe5 12. fxe5 O-O 13. Bg5 $16) (8... Nh5 9.
Nf3 Bg4 10. Be2 $16 {1-0 (15) Soulas,P-Vuillemin,G Finland 1995}) (8... dxe5 9.
fxe5 Ng4 (9... Nfd7 10. Nf3 Bg7 11. e6 {Transposes to 8...Nfd7.}) 10. e6 h5 (
10... Qh4+ 11. g3 Qh5 12. Be2 f5 13. Ne4 fxe4 14. Bxg4 Qe5 15. e7 $18 {1-0 (70)
Castelfranchi,C (2165)-Volpinari,D (2050) Bratto 2003}) 11. Qa4+ Ke7 12. Bg5+
f6 13. Bf4 $18 {1-0 (20) Cornette,M (2548)-Rudd,J (2290) London 2011}) (8...
Qe7 9. Qe2 Nfd7 10. Ne4 $18) 9. Nf3 Bg7 (9... dxe5 10. fxe5 Bg7 11. e6 fxe6 12.
dxe6 Qe7 (12... Nf6 13. Qxd8+ Kxd8 14. Ng5 $18) 13. Nd5 Qxe6+ 14. Be2 O-O {
1-0 (54) Vitor,A (2367)-Santos,A (2265) Lisbon 2007} (14... Qc6 15. O-O Bd4+
16. Nxd4 Qxd5 17. Nf5 $18 {1-0 (35) Shamkovich,L-Kolobov,Y Moscow (Russia) 1962
}) 15. Nc7 $18) 10. Ne4 $1 dxe5 11. Nd6+ Kf8 (11... Ke7 12. Ng5 Qb6 13. Ngxf7
Rf8 14. Qg4 $18 {1-0 (49) Jaunooby,A (2178)-Gonzalvez Perales,J (1984) Caleta
2013}) 12. Ng5 exf4 13. Ndxf7 Qe7+ 14. Be2 Ne5 15. Nxh8 Qxg5 16. O-O Kg8 17.
Bxf4 Qe7 18. d6 $18 {Smirnov,L-Volovich,A Moscow (Russia) 1959}) 7. f4 $1 ({
Black is wishing White plays} 7. a4 {to reach a version of the Modern Benoni
where the Taimanov Attack doesn't exist.} g6) 7... Bg4 ({In case of} 7... b5 $2
{White's initiative is unstopable.} 8. e5 $1 dxe5 (8... Qe7 9. Qe2 Nfd7 (9...
Ng4 10. Nf3 dxe5 11. fxe5 b4 12. Ne4 Nxe5 13. d6 Nxf3+ {1-0 (31) Schebler,
G-Zrinscak,S Krefeld 1986} 14. Qxf3 Qe6 15. Be2 Bb7 16. Nf6+ $18) 10. Nf3 Bb7 {
Liptay,L-Cifuentes,A Prague 1966} 11. g3 Nb6 (11... g6 12. Ne4 {Winning in the
spot.}) 12. Bh3 $18) 9. fxe5 b4 (9... Ng4 10. Nf3 Nd7 11. Bf4 g6 12. h3 Nh6 13.
g4 Nb6 14. Qd2 b4 15. Ne4 Ng8 16. d6 $18 {[#] White's got a dream position in
the game Morchiashvili,B (2427)-Orakci,M Izmir 2008.}) (9... Nfd7 10. Nf3 Nb6
11. d6 $1 {Black's lack of space makes it hard for his pieces to effectively
join the battle.} Bb7 12. Be2 Qd7 13. O-O Qc6 14. Nh4 N8d7 15. Bf3 Qc8 16. e6 {
White took advantage of its better development opening the position of her
opponent's king, Ordaz Valdes, L (2363)-Hernandez Moya, Y (2227) Pinar del Rio
2014.}) 10. exf6 bxc3 11. Qe2+ Kd7 12. fxg7 Bxg7 13. Qg4+ {Was winning for
White in the game Gazioglu, H (1959)-Gunes, A (1711) Antalya 2013.}) 8. Qa4+ {
With this move, White confronts Black with serious problems. Even though it
seems that} (8. Be2 {is equally playable, and perhaps simpler.} Bxe2 9. Qxe2 g6
{1-0 (25) De Souza,M (2405)-Nagashima,C (2050) Santa Barbara d'Oeste 1998} 10.
e5 $1 $146 dxe5 11. d6 $1 Bxd6 12. fxe5 O-O 13. Nf3 Re8 14. Bg5 Bxe5 15. Nxe5
Nc6 16. O-O Rxe5 17. Bxf6 Rxe2 18. Bxd8 Rxb2 19. Bf6 $18) 8... Bd7 (8... Nbd7
$2 9. h3) (8... Nfd7 $2 9. g3 Be7 10. h3 Bh5 11. g4 $18 {1-0 (31) Mecking,H 
(2562)-Rodriguez Vila,A (2511) Campinas 2011}) ({Though} 8... b5 {looks like a
desperate attempt and has never been played, it might be a good practical
attempt.} 9. Bxb5+ axb5 10. Qxa8 b4 11. Nce2 Nxe4 12. Nf3 Be7 13. O-O O-O 14.
a3 {With a clear plus for White.}) 9. Qc2 Qe7 {Black tries to control e5 with
this awkward move.} (9... g6 {The attempt to give the position a Modern Benoni
character fails to} 10. e5 dxe5 11. fxe5 Ng4 ({The entretaining} 11... Qe7 12.
Nf3 Bg7 13. Bg5 h6 14. Bc4 hxg5 15. d6 Qd8 16. Bxf7+ Kxf7 17. Nxg5+ Kf8 18. O-O
$18 {is hopeless for Black.}) 12. Qe2 $16) 10. Nf3 Bg4 ({The bold} 10... b5 {
leads Black to a lost position.} 11. e5 b4 12. Bc4 bxc3 13. O-O $18) 11. Be2
Nbd7 12. O-O Bxf3 13. Bxf3 g6 {[#]} 14. e5 $1 dxe5 15. d6 Qxd6 16. Bxb7 Rb8 17.
fxe5 Qd4+ 18. Kh1 Rxb7 19. exf6 Bd6 20. Bh6 $18 {Krysa,L - Munoz Pantoja,M
Barcelona 2017} *

