Nxe5 Bxe5 34. Qe3 $1 {With advantage for White.}) 32. Nf3 Re4 33. Ng5 Rxd7 34.
Nxe4 fxe4 35. Kh1 {With a clear edge for White.}) 29. d7 Nxd7 30. Rad1 Qxe4 31.
Bxd7 Rcd8 32. Bxe8 Rxe8 33. Qd2 {And White’s exchange advantage may prove
enough to acquire a winning advantage.} *

